Cinco de Mayo is a Mexican holiday that celebrates the date of the Mexican army’s victory over France at the Battle of Puebla during the Franco-Mexican War in 1862. Americans traditionally use it as a day to stuff ourselves with Mexican food and party. Here are ways for you to enjoy the holiday. Fiesta: A Cinco de Mayo Party: The party on Spa Beach at the St. Pete Pier will have authentic entertainment, tacos, tequila,  margaritas, a mariachi band and performance by Sol Caribe, activities  and games for the entire family. Get tickets and details at fiestastpete.com. $10-$20; VIP $55-$75. 1-9 p.m. April 30. St. Pete Pier, 800 Second Ave. NE, St. Petersburg. 727-822-7437. Pre-Cinco de Mayo Bar Crawl: Since Cinco de Mayo falls on a Thursday this year, these pre-Cinco bar crawls will have tacos, tequila and drink specials at several downtown St. Petersburg and Tampa bars. Each will also have free welcome shots, drink specials and bar games. $25 each and register at downtowncrawlers.com. Cinco de Drinko Bar Crawl: Join Top Shelf Crawls for a nine-stop crawl with taco and drink specials, Cinco beads, souvenir koozie and no cover at bars. $9.99-$17.99. 4 p.m.-1 a.m. April 30. Tryst Gastro Lounge, 240 Beach Drive NE, St. Petersburg. 727-821-4567. Sip! Dip! Ole!: No time to siesta. Round up your amigos for this fiesta with $5 margaritas all night, a complimentary taco bar, $2.25 bottled beer and live music by Partners in Crime. $20-$25. 5 p.m. April 30. Bogota Kitchen and Bar, 917 11th St., Palm Harbor. 727-754-5047. Cinco de Mayo Publix: Find a hidden avocado illustration in the aisles, show it to an associate and win a gift card. Also, all day specials on burrito bowls, Mexican pizza and drinks. No cover (food/drink additional). 7 a.m.-10 p.m. May 5. Publix Greenwise Market at Water Street, 555 Channelside Drive, Tampa. 813-221-4121. Also taking place at several other Greenwise locations across the area. Contact yours to see if they are participating. Cinco De Mayo All Day